Not sure who needs to hear this but stop trying to build relationships with someone who doesn’t want you around. There actions are everything, see how they talk and act with other friends and loved ones. It’s different right? Or don’t invite you to things or not interested in uplifting you. Don’t waste your time trying please them and make something more then what it is. Be around people who wants to be there, communicate with you and speak highly of you. Let those failing relationships die so others can be taken more seriously. Love yourself enough to be treated well by others. Love yourself enough to be ok to be alone with your awesome self. Sometimes being alone help you really evaluate different situations. Because sometimes your the problem. Secretly. They alone time is medicine for your soul. Be your own best friend… get real creative and rest and then ask yourself is there relationship really worth it? If so reach out and tell them how you feel or drop it until it happens. 😊 real life stuff we all deal with just wanted to share 🙏🏾😉 yea but you first!

Hey my loves question…. Are you a fan of DELICIOUS SPICY CHICKEN?

If so, you have to try Houston Texas Hot Chicken @hhc here in Tempe Arizona!!!!!!

HHC has been here for 1 year already and has quickly become one of the city’s most popular hot chicken joints. Especially for the ASU college students. It all started in Vegas now franchising all over the US. 

First up, we have the Mild Chicken sandwich and a medium chicken strip combo, which is simply irresistible… you get both. The chicken is Artisan style and cooked to perfection, with a crispy exterior and juicy meat that oozes out with every bite. It’s served with a side of seasoned crinkle fries and HHC special dipping sauce that will leave your taste buds dancing. I even asked for ranch too and didn’t even use it!

Next, we have the Cookie Crumble MilkShake. This is the perfect dessert to follow up on after a spicy meal. It’s a creamy, vanilla/chocolate shake that has pieces of Pucks cookies mixed in. I tried the cookies and cream cookie milkshake with vanilla & chocolate it was simply 🤤 x5.

But this place isn’t just about the food… it’s also about the atmosphere. The vibe is laid-back and fun, with a casual, family-friendly feel. The staff are friendly and welcoming, thank you Jay for the hospitality.

So, whether you’re looking for a juicy spicy chicken meal, a sweet cookie or cookie milkshake to cool you down, or just a fun place to hang out with friends, @HHC is the place to be. Come down and experience the delicious flavors for yourself!

📍 927 E University Drive Tempe AZ 
- across from @tempeimprov

Of course, I can’t forget about the rides! The Arizona State Fair is home to some amazing rides, including a massive Ferris wheel and there new Raptor high-speed roller coaster. These rides are always a hit with people of all ages.

Overall, the Arizona State Fair is a great way to spend an afternoon or weekend. With so many fun activities and attractions, it’s sure to be a memorable experience for everyone involved. So mark your calendars and get ready to head to the state fair it’s here until OCTOBER 29🎉

Hey guys, 
Self love is the most important thing in our lives. It is the fuel that drives us towards our goals and helps us overcome obstacles. Without self love, we cannot give love to others. In this world, we are constantly bombarded with negativity and pressure to be someone we are not. It’s important to remember that we are enough just the way we are.

I have always loved solo traveling. It gives me the freedom to explore myself and the world around me. I don’t have to worry about anyone else’s opinion or expectations. All I have to do is focus on myself and what I want to achieve. The clarity ✨

I have learned that self love isn’t just about putting on a happy face for the world. It’s about embracing our true selves and living a fulfilling life. It’s about making choices that are good for us and our health, and it’s about standing up for ourselves when we are hurt or judged.
So, I encourage everyone to practice self love. Take care of yourself, be kind to yourself, and don’t forget to hug yourself and take that trip you deserve it!

Located in Old San Juan, Puerto Rico. This restaurant offers rum-infused cocktails and gourmet dishes that blend the island’s unique flavors. Try the Baquine, a drink made with Rums of Puerto Rico añejo rum, fresh lime juice, raspberries and rose infusion syrup ,Crème de Violet, rose water and aqua-fava. Enjoy the succulent skirt steak called Churrasco in PR. Along with starters like the chicken chicharrón, and don’t miss out on trying the Fried Cheese Bites, a traditional dish that showcases the island’s culinary heritage. La Casita de Rones is the perfect spot to immerse yourself in Puerto Rican culture and indulge in a delicious dining experience right by the ocean.
